sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    %% ============================================================
    %% Flow 1: InferenceService Model Serving (Standard Mode)
    %% ============================================================

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,ObjStorage: Flow 1 - InferenceService Model Serving (Standard Mode)

        participant Client as External Client
        participant Gateway as Gateway / Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+
        participant AuthProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
        participant ModelServer as Model Server<br/>Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        participant ObjStorage as Object Storage<br/>(S3/GCS/Azure/HF/OCI)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

        Note over ModelServer,ObjStorage: Init Phase (before serving)
        ModelServer-->>ObjStorage: storage-initializer downloads model<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS 1.2+ | Provider credentials

        Note over Client,ModelServer: Inference Phase
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS 1.2+ | Bearer token (optional)
        Gateway->>AuthProxy: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 | TLS
        AuthProxy->>AuthProxy: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(validates Bearer token)
        AuthProxy->>ModelServer: Forward to model server<br/>HTTP/8080 | None (localhost)
        ModelServer-->>AuthProxy: Prediction response
        AuthProxy-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON prediction result
    end

    %% ============================================================
    %% Flow 2: LLMInferenceService Model Serving
    %% ============================================================

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Client2,Prometheus: Flow 2 - LLMInferenceService Model Serving

        participant Client2 as External Client
        participant GW as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+
        participant EPP as Scheduler (EPP)<br/>9002/TCP gRPC<br/>TLS (self-signed)
        participant Workload as Workload Pod<br/>(vLLM)<br/>8000/TCP HTTPS
        participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Monitoring

        Client2->>GW: POST /v1/completions<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS 1.2+ | Kuadrant AuthPolicy (OCP)
        GW->>GW: HTTPRoute matches<br/>InferencePool backend
        GW->>EPP: Route via InferencePool<br/>gRPC/9002 | TLS (self-signed)
        EPP->>EPP: Schedule request<br/>(select optimal pod)
        EPP->>Workload: Forward to workload pod<br/>HTTPS/8000 | TLS (self-signed or service-ca)
        Workload-->>EPP: LLM completion response
        EPP-->>GW: Response
        GW-->>Client2: JSON completion result

        Note over Prometheus,Workload: Monitoring
        Prometheus->>Workload: Scrape vLLM metrics (PodMonitor)<br/>HTTPS/8000 | TLS (InsecureSkipVerify)
        Prometheus->>EPP: Scrape scheduler metrics (ServiceMonitor)<br/>HTTPS/metrics | TLS | Bearer token (SA secret)
    end

    %% ============================================================
    %% Flow 3: InferenceGraph Routing
    %% ============================================================

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Client3,TargetISVC: Flow 3 - InferenceGraph DAG Routing

        participant Client3 as External Client
        participant RouterPod as kserve-router<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Optional TLS
        participant TargetISVC as Target InferenceService(s)<br/>Various ports<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

        Client3->>RouterPod: POST / (inference request)<br/>HTTP/8080 | Optional TLS | Optional Bearer token
        RouterPod->>RouterPod: TokenReview + SAR<br/>(if auth enabled)
        RouterPod->>TargetISVC: Step 1: Call model A<br/>HTTP/HTTPS | Istio mTLS (if in mesh)
        TargetISVC-->>RouterPod: Step 1 result
        RouterPod->>TargetISVC: Step 2: Call model B<br/>(Sequence/Splitter/Ensemble/Switch)
        TargetISVC-->>RouterPod: Step 2 result
        RouterPod->>RouterPod: Merge/route results<br/>(DAG logic)
        RouterPod-->>Client3: Combined inference result
    end
